{
  "text": "For example, careful thought must be given to the selection of specific parameter values to manipulate. An infinite number of ways exist for distributions to depart from homoscedasticity. How does the author select a realistic sample of distributions to examine? Although there is no simple answer, some sources can supply useful evidence of the types of distributions obtained in actual empirical work in the behavioral sciences (e.g., [CITATION_1] . [CITATION_2] provided an exafciple of how this type of information can be incorporated into the de-sign of simulation studies. Of course, previous simulation studies in related areas can also provide a useful framework for selecting conditions to simulate.",
